# Soft65C02 MCP (Claude Code / project context)

This project uses the **`soft65c02`** MCP server to run **Soft65C02 tester DSL** against a virtual 65C02.

## MCP tools (names may vary by client)

- **`dsl_session_execute`** — persistent emulator session (preferred for debugging).
- **`dsl_execute`** — fresh machine each call.
- **`dsl_session_reset`**, **`dsl_session_checkpoint_*`** — session lifecycle and restart survival.
- **`dsl_parse`**, **`dsl_memory_rom_reference`** — helpers.

## Your job

Translate the user’s **natural language** (load file, ROM at address, run from PC, assert memory) into **valid DSL**. Do **not** require the user to paste DSL unless they want to.

**Syntax and examples:** read **`soft65c02_tester/documentation.md`** from the Soft65C02 checkout (set a path below if this file lives elsewhere).

Suggested doc path (edit to match this machine):

`@/absolute/path/to/soft65c02/soft65c02_tester/documentation.md`

## Windows

Use absolute paths in MCP config; in DSL quoted filenames may use `/` or escaped `\\`.
